1
00:00:00,931 --> 00:00:02,241
You're moving in with Tuo?

2
00:00:09,034 --> 00:00:10,034
Yes.

3
00:00:12,724 --> 00:00:15,068
His dad decided to sell the
house and move to Kaohsiung.

4
00:00:15,758 --> 00:00:17,413
But Tuo wanted to stay.

5
00:00:17,413 --> 00:00:18,964
His dad told him he was on his own.

6
00:00:21,447 --> 00:00:22,447
I see.

7
00:00:26,447 --> 00:00:27,792
The company I'm interning at now...

8
00:00:27,793 --> 00:00:29,103
is too far from home.

9
00:00:29,103 --> 00:00:30,654
Commuting to school and my internship...

10
00:00:30,655 --> 00:00:32,103
takes up so much time.

11
00:00:32,344 --> 00:00:33,619
We're not sleeping well.

12
00:00:34,275 --> 00:00:36,102
We're always dozing off in class.

13
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:38,862
So I was thinking...

14
00:00:38,862 --> 00:00:40,344
Tuo and I could live together.

15
00:00:40,896 --> 00:00:42,758
Find a place that's
convenient for both of us.

16
00:00:45,068 --> 00:00:46,206
An internship is only temporary.

17
00:00:46,206 --> 00:00:48,068
Just tough it out for
a bit, and it'll be over.

18
00:00:48,240 --> 00:00:49,068
Honey.

19
00:00:49,068 --> 00:00:51,516
It's a three-hour round trip
every day. Could you stand that?

20
00:00:52,585 --> 00:00:54,033
It takes that long?

21
00:00:54,034 --> 00:00:55,103
Yeah, Dad.

22
00:00:55,103 --> 00:00:56,551
You're always saying...

23
00:00:56,551 --> 00:00:58,309
how Tuo is more
independent and mature.

24
00:00:58,862 --> 00:01:01,310
If I move in with him,
I can learn from him.

25
00:01:02,516 --> 00:01:03,826
Yushu left.

26
00:01:03,827 --> 00:01:06,172
And now even Junxi wants to move out.

27
00:01:09,896 --> 00:01:12,655
Yushu ran away from
home because you two fought.

28
00:01:12,655 --> 00:01:14,689
Junxi is discussing this with you.

29
00:01:14,689 --> 00:01:16,344
They're completely different things, okay?

30
00:01:29,343 --> 00:01:30,723
Alright, alright. I agree.

31
00:01:33,827 --> 00:01:35,137
Thanks, Dad.

32
00:01:44,551 --> 00:01:47,551
(Episode 8: His Lie, His Panic)

33
00:02:46,931 --> 00:02:53,931
"Secret Lover"

34
00:02:57,723 --> 00:02:59,034
Daddy.

35
00:03:08,447 --> 00:03:09,343
Little bro.

36
00:03:09,343 --> 00:03:10,102
Bro.

37
00:03:10,103 --> 00:03:11,103
You...

38
00:03:18,343 --> 00:03:19,378
Tuo.

39
00:03:19,378 --> 00:03:20,481
Yushu.

40
00:03:20,481 --> 00:03:21,619
Long time no see.

41
00:03:27,481 --> 00:03:28,792
Are you really moving back in?

42
00:03:29,516 --> 00:03:30,792
Well...

43
00:03:31,447 --> 00:03:33,240
I had a run of bad luck..

44
00:03:33,241 --> 00:03:35,516
Because of the pandemic, my
braised-food shop went under.

45
00:03:36,275 --> 00:03:38,723
I couldn't find a job after that.

46
00:03:38,723 --> 00:03:40,517
I was three months behind on rent.

47
00:03:41,206 --> 00:03:41,965
Now...

48
00:03:41,965 --> 00:03:43,448
my landlord kicked me out.

49
00:03:44,309 --> 00:03:44,964
What about my sister-in-law?

50
00:03:44,965 --> 00:03:46,068
We're divorced.

51
00:03:47,931 --> 00:03:49,206
A month ago.

52
00:03:50,275 --> 00:03:51,757
I'm counting on you, bro.

53
00:03:52,655 --> 00:03:54,137
Help me look after Xiao Zhou.

54
00:03:56,137 --> 00:03:56,861
Look.

55
00:03:56,861 --> 00:03:57,896
Clothes, snacks...

56
00:03:57,965 --> 00:03:59,378
toys, utensils, everything.

57
00:03:59,378 --> 00:04:00,413
Just watch him for one day.

58
00:04:02,516 --> 00:04:04,413
Let me go back and have
a proper talk with Dad.

59
00:04:04,413 --> 00:04:05,654
With Xiao Zhou there...

60
00:04:05,655 --> 00:04:07,827
Dad might be easier to talk to.

61
00:04:08,516 --> 00:04:10,102
We just moved in ourselves.

62
00:04:10,103 --> 00:04:10,861
And we haven't even unpacked yet.

63
00:04:10,861 --> 00:04:12,827
You know what Dad's temper is like.

64
00:04:12,827 --> 00:04:14,758
What if he tries to hit me?

65
00:04:14,758 --> 00:04:16,758
Is your big brother's
pride more important...

66
00:04:16,758 --> 00:04:18,241
or is unpacking more important?

67
00:04:19,827 --> 00:04:21,310
I knew you were the best.

68
00:04:26,413 --> 00:04:28,171
Then you need to talk to Dad properly.

69
00:04:28,172 --> 00:04:29,206
Don't get into a fight.

70
00:04:31,793 --> 00:04:33,793
This is the signature
braised food from my shop.

71
00:04:33,793 --> 00:04:34,862
Help yourselves.

72
00:04:36,793 --> 00:04:37,930
It's gross.

73
00:04:37,931 --> 00:04:39,172
Don't eat it.

74
00:04:40,723 --> 00:04:42,137
Son.

75
00:04:42,723 --> 00:04:44,482
Okay, that's all for
today. Class dismissed.

76
00:04:47,655 --> 00:04:49,930
Now that Yushu is back...

77
00:04:49,931 --> 00:04:51,723
his dad must be giving
him a real hard time.

78
00:04:51,723 --> 00:04:52,585
That's what he's afraid of.

79
00:04:52,585 --> 00:04:54,620
That's why he asked Junxi
to help watch Xiao Zhou.

80
00:04:54,862 --> 00:04:56,241
Xiao Yang, are you ready?

81
00:04:57,413 --> 00:04:59,619
Hey, busy bee. Want to grab a bite?

82
00:04:59,620 --> 00:05:01,757
I have to go help Junxi look after a kid.
ORGAN

83
00:05:03,068 --> 00:05:05,034
A kid?

84
00:05:05,034 --> 00:05:06,206
Who'd Junxi have a kid with?

85
00:05:07,068 --> 00:05:08,240
His nephew.

86
00:05:09,413 --> 00:05:10,654
Just kidding.

87
00:05:14,413 --> 00:05:15,413
Tuo.

88
00:05:15,965 --> 00:05:17,862
Junxi's been having a tough time lately.

89
00:05:17,862 --> 00:05:20,275
You should help him
out more with Xiao Zhou.

90
00:05:20,275 --> 00:05:21,275
What do you mean?

91
00:05:27,655 --> 00:05:28,689
Xiao Zhou.

92
00:05:28,689 --> 00:05:30,689
That's Uncle Tuo's ruler. It's not a toy.

93
00:05:30,689 --> 00:05:31,655
I don't care!

94
00:05:31,655 --> 00:05:32,723
Walk slowly.

95
00:05:32,723 --> 00:05:33,758
You'll fall.

96
00:05:41,793 --> 00:05:43,379
Stop jumping around.

97
00:05:44,206 --> 00:05:45,206
It's dangerous.

98
00:05:46,172 --> 00:05:46,965
Okay.

99
00:05:46,965 --> 00:05:48,068
Uncle's gonna get you!

100
00:06:03,689 --> 00:06:04,689
Gotcha!

101
00:06:11,413 --> 00:06:13,206
Pay your rent, or get out!

102
00:06:13,206 --> 00:06:14,654
Just who are you?

103
00:06:14,655 --> 00:06:16,137
Landlord-Man.

104
00:06:17,655 --> 00:06:18,620
Landlord-Man.

105
00:06:18,620 --> 00:06:20,688
Who's the landlord?

106
00:06:24,516 --> 00:06:25,447
You're back.

107
00:06:25,447 --> 00:06:26,447
Time for dinner.

108
00:06:41,620 --> 00:06:42,792
Let's go wash our hands and eat.

109
00:06:42,793 --> 00:06:44,137
Okay.

110
00:06:49,551 --> 00:06:50,482
Can you eat by yourself?

111
00:06:50,482 --> 00:06:51,619
I can. I'm five.

112
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,034
Here you go.

113
00:07:06,723 --> 00:07:07,723
Junxi.

114
00:07:15,103 --> 00:07:16,723
During our liberal arts
class today, Xiao Yang said...

115
00:07:16,723 --> 00:07:17,585
Uncle.

116
00:07:17,585 --> 00:07:18,723
Let's go to the park after we eat.

117
00:07:18,723 --> 00:07:20,861
My dad always takes me to the park.

118
00:07:20,862 --> 00:07:21,758
Okay.

119
00:07:21,758 --> 00:07:23,413
We'll go after you're done eating.

120
00:07:28,103 --> 00:07:29,689
Take your time.

121
00:07:32,827 --> 00:07:33,999
Xiao Zhou, catch!

122
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:35,000
Here.

123
00:07:36,793 --> 00:07:37,793
Here it comes!

124
00:07:38,896 --> 00:07:40,275
Great job!

125
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,000
Here it comes!

126
00:07:45,343 --> 00:07:46,343
Go get it.

127
00:07:47,378 --> 00:07:48,378
Go on, get it!

128
00:07:50,551 --> 00:07:51,861
Hurry!

129
00:08:05,447 --> 00:08:06,447
Again!

130
00:08:10,447 --> 00:08:11,723
Look, look.

131
00:08:11,723 --> 00:08:13,379
The airplane's taking off!

132
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:22,137
To your left.

133
00:08:23,827 --> 00:08:24,827
Look over there.

134
00:08:27,413 --> 00:08:29,033
You little rascal.

135
00:08:29,034 --> 00:08:30,378
That's mine!

136
00:08:37,965 --> 00:08:38,758
Come on, come on!

137
00:08:38,758 --> 00:08:39,758
Come on!

138
00:08:40,275 --> 00:08:41,654
Try and get me! Try and get me!

139
00:08:45,102 --> 00:08:46,171
Retreat!

140
00:08:48,309 --> 00:08:50,102
Wow, you're pretty good.

141
00:08:50,102 --> 00:08:51,171
Backup!

142
00:08:58,447 --> 00:09:00,137
You're it!

143
00:09:00,137 --> 00:09:01,516
Again!

144
00:09:12,034 --> 00:09:13,378
Uncle, a kiss.

145
00:09:13,896 --> 00:09:15,034
No kissing.

146
00:09:15,481 --> 00:09:16,481
He's mine.

147
00:09:16,965 --> 00:09:19,000
Mine. Uncle is mine.
(Watch on www.kisskh.ovh to support Admin)

148
00:09:19,413 --> 00:09:20,206
Mine.

149
00:09:20,206 --> 00:09:21,034
He's mine!

150
00:09:21,034 --> 00:09:22,861
Uncle is mine, right?

151
00:09:26,034 --> 00:09:27,965
What are you saying in front of a child?

152
00:09:27,965 --> 00:09:29,551
Come on, let's go take a bath.

153
00:10:24,655 --> 00:10:26,310
He's finally asleep.

154
00:10:36,206 --> 00:10:38,827
An angel when he's asleep,
a little devil when he's awake.

155
00:10:39,172 --> 00:10:41,344
I don't know how my brother
raises him all on his own.

156
00:10:48,172 --> 00:10:49,172
I want some too.

157
00:11:23,793 --> 00:11:26,793
Xiao Yang mentioned you're having
some issues with your internship.

158
00:12:05,481 --> 00:12:07,171
You haven't...

159
00:12:07,172 --> 00:12:08,585
looked at me all day.

160
00:12:27,585 --> 00:12:29,033
This isn't right.

161
00:12:29,585 --> 00:12:31,275
If we keep it down, no one will find out.

162
00:12:42,102 --> 00:12:43,758
I have to pee.

163
00:13:00,827 --> 00:13:02,241
Uncle.

164
00:13:04,620 --> 00:13:06,275
I have to pee.

165
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,551
Uncle, I have to pee.

166
00:13:11,724 --> 00:13:13,861
Uncle, hurry! I'm going to burst!

167
00:13:16,240 --> 00:13:17,930
I have to pee.

168
00:13:25,447 --> 00:13:26,516
Hello?

169
00:13:28,551 --> 00:13:30,309
Bro, are you coming to get Xiao Zhou?

170
00:13:31,793 --> 00:13:32,551
Okay.

171
00:13:32,551 --> 00:13:33,620
See you in a bit.

172
00:13:36,655 --> 00:13:37,655
Let's go.

173
00:13:42,516 --> 00:13:44,206
Dad really hit you?

174
00:13:46,620 --> 00:13:47,620
Yeah.

175
00:13:48,275 --> 00:13:50,344
He grabbed a stick and
was going to beat me with it.

176
00:13:50,861 --> 00:13:52,516
Luckily, I was good reflexes.

177
00:13:52,516 --> 00:13:53,826
He only got me once.

178
00:13:55,068 --> 00:13:56,792
And that's what happened.

179
00:13:56,793 --> 00:13:57,620
You ungrateful son!

180
00:13:57,620 --> 00:13:58,688
How dare you come back!

181
00:13:58,689 --> 00:13:59,481
J...

182
00:13:59,481 --> 00:14:00,481
Honey, stop.

183
00:14:05,585 --> 00:14:06,481
Come on.

184
00:14:06,481 --> 00:14:08,550
We're going to stay at
Grandpa and Grandma's.

185
00:14:08,931 --> 00:14:10,413
Say thank you to your uncles.

186
00:14:10,413 --> 00:14:12,481
They worked really hard
taking care of you yesterday.

187
00:14:12,481 --> 00:14:14,792
That's not true! I was very good and brave.

188
00:14:17,137 --> 00:14:18,792
I slept all by myself at night.

189
00:14:18,793 --> 00:14:21,586
Not lik
like the uncles, who
cuddle when you sleep.

190
00:14:29,931 --> 00:14:32,379
I had Xiao Zhou sleep
in my room last night.

191
00:14:35,551 --> 00:14:37,826
You could have just slept with Xiao Zhou.

192
00:14:37,827 --> 00:14:39,310
Why'd you need Tuo?

193
00:14:42,620 --> 00:14:43,757
You two..

194
00:14:43,758 --> 00:14:44,930
Are you, like, a thing?

195
00:14:49,551 --> 00:14:50,792
You're overthinking it.

196
00:14:50,793 --> 00:14:52,206
We're just regular friends.

197
00:15:00,068 --> 00:15:01,516
Is that so?

198
00:15:04,620 --> 00:15:05,516
Well, we're heading out.

199
00:15:06,447 --> 00:15:08,688
Bye, uncle. Bye, Uncle Tuo.

200
00:15:08,689 --> 00:15:09,792
Bye.

201
00:15:09,793 --> 00:15:10,793
See you.

202
00:15:11,206 --> 00:15:12,378
Okay, let's go.

203
00:15:13,068 --> 00:15:14,827
We're going to see Grandpa and Grandma.

204
00:15:15,861 --> 00:15:16,930
Off we go.

205
00:15:21,689 --> 00:15:23,379
Bye.

206
00:15:29,102 --> 00:15:30,378
My brother didn't notice, did he?

207
00:15:31,931 --> 00:15:32,931
Of course not.

208
00:15:47,827 --> 00:15:49,309
You've been living
together for almost a month,

209
00:15:49,309 --> 00:15:50,826
and you're just now inviting us over?

210
00:15:51,378 --> 00:15:52,688
Everyone's been busy.

211
00:15:52,689 --> 00:15:54,378
And you two are hard to pin down.

212
00:15:54,378 --> 00:15:57,344
It's fine. Celebrating your one-month
"cohabit-aversary" isn't bad either.

213
00:15:58,931 --> 00:16:01,620
Junxi, how'd you get your
parents to agree to this?

214
00:16:06,931 --> 00:16:07,931
Well...

215
00:16:09,827 --> 00:16:11,930
Don't tell me you told your family...

216
00:16:11,931 --> 00:16:14,448
you're just roommates, learning
to be independent or something.

217
00:16:18,344 --> 00:16:19,654
Seriously? I guessed it?

218
00:16:20,172 --> 00:16:21,551
That excuse-is used by
nine out of ten couples

219
00:16:21,551 --> 00:16:22,688
who move in together.

220
00:16:22,724 --> 00:16:23,481
He Youmei.
- So old-school.

221
00:16:23,481 --> 00:16:24,481
Such a classic move.

222
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:26,068
Have some fried chicken.

223
00:16:27,240 --> 00:16:28,240
I'll go get some beer.

224
00:17:17,309 --> 00:17:18,344
Don't mind He Youmei.

225
00:17:18,344 --> 00:17:19,619
That's just how she talks.

226
00:17:25,689 --> 00:17:26,758
What's wrong?

227
00:17:28,896 --> 00:17:30,275
It's nothing.

228
00:17:31,551 --> 00:17:33,481
You tell me to share everything with you,

229
00:17:33,481 --> 00:17:34,723
but what about you?

230
00:17:34,723 --> 00:17:36,344
You never tell me when something's wrong.

231
00:17:36,481 --> 00:17:38,206
What could possibly be wrong?

232
00:17:39,206 --> 00:17:41,068
Aren't you getting
bullied at your internship?

233
00:17:45,723 --> 00:17:47,448
Xiao Yang told you.

234
00:17:49,068 --> 00:17:50,896
Was that a message from
your company just now?

235
00:18:22,137 --> 00:18:23,206
I'm so hungry.

236
00:18:23,206 --> 00:18:25,137
We left before I could even get full.

237
00:18:27,068 --> 00:18:28,930
That's because you couldn't
keep your mouth shut.

238
00:18:28,931 --> 00:18:30,965
You ruined a perfectly good party.

239
00:18:30,965 --> 00:18:32,275
What did I say?

240
00:18:32,275 --> 00:18:34,964
They're the ones with a guilty
conscience. How is it my fault?

241
00:18:34,965 --> 00:18:36,206
The way they're dating in secret,

242
00:18:36,206 --> 00:18:39,103
they're basically planning an
exit strategy for their relationship.

243
00:18:39,103 --> 00:18:41,378
It's not like they're trying
to hide it on purpose.

244
00:18:42,931 --> 00:18:44,619
Who knows?

245
00:18:44,619 --> 00:18:46,723
A relationship like that is
bound to have problems.

246
00:18:47,344 --> 00:18:48,999
Take it from someone who's been there.

247
00:18:49,862 --> 00:18:51,724
If you don't believe me,
just you wait and see.

248
00:18:53,172 --> 00:18:56,206
A love that can't be spoken
aloud can't withstand any real tests.

249
00:18:56,655 --> 00:18:58,723
It's like ice cream.

250
00:18:58,723 --> 00:19:01,103
You take it out into the
sun, and it melts in an instant.

251
00:19:02,344 --> 00:19:03,826
And then there's nothing left.

252
00:19:05,068 --> 00:19:06,344
He Youmei.

253
00:19:07,344 --> 00:19:09,688
Did something happen to you in the past?

254
00:19:15,655 --> 00:19:17,103
Surprised you, huh?

255
00:19:17,723 --> 00:19:20,137
I just read all that stuff in a comic book.

256
00:19:20,137 --> 00:19:21,965
I'm starving. Let's go get some ramen.

257
00:19:22,481 --> 00:19:24,826
I don't like it when you lie.

258
00:19:24,827 --> 00:19:26,689
If it hurts, it hurts. If
you want to cry, cry.

259
00:19:27,378 --> 00:19:29,999
Smiling and saying you're fine
doesn't actually make you fine.

260
00:19:31,344 --> 00:19:33,068
If I say it hurts,

261
00:19:33,068 --> 00:19:34,792
will you kiss it and make it better?

262
00:19:37,172 --> 00:19:38,172
Make it better?

263
00:19:38,585 --> 00:19:39,792
Like this.

264
00:19:57,447 --> 00:19:58,861
What's there to make better?

265
00:19:59,862 --> 00:20:01,516
If you don't face your wounds,

266
00:20:01,516 --> 00:20:03,378
they won't disappear, and they won't heal.

267
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:06,206
No matter how many
times you kiss it, it'll still hurt.

268
00:20:09,619 --> 00:20:11,826
If you keep this up, I might fall for you.

269
00:20:13,619 --> 00:20:15,137
Idiot.

270
00:20:21,034 --> 00:20:22,861
So, which ramen place do you want to go to?

271
00:20:23,862 --> 00:20:25,206
The one at the internet cafe.

272
00:20:26,275 --> 00:20:27,826
Are you crying?

273
00:20:27,827 --> 00:20:29,240
No, I'm not.

274
00:20:29,240 --> 00:20:30,551
He Youmei, you're a crybaby.

275
00:20:30,585 --> 00:20:31,033
I'm not!

276
00:20:31,034 --> 00:20:32,344
Your nose is running.

277
00:20:32,344 --> 00:20:33,206
No, it's not!

278
00:20:33,206 --> 00:20:33,965
Yes, it is.

279
00:20:33,965 --> 00:20:34,862
See for yourself.

280
00:20:34,862 --> 00:20:36,103
I want to eat...

281
00:20:36,103 --> 00:20:36,654
Spicy.

282
00:20:36,723 --> 00:20:37,585
Let's get spicy ramen.

283
00:20:37,585 --> 00:20:38,688
You're blushing.

284
00:21:06,068 --> 00:21:07,516
I told my brother

285
00:21:07,516 --> 00:21:09,930
that I fell asleep in your
room playing video games.

286
00:21:09,931 --> 00:21:11,172
I told him not to overthink it.

287
00:21:15,240 --> 00:21:16,172
Or should I say...

288
00:21:16,172 --> 00:21:18,103
I'm used to sleeping with a stuffed toy,

289
00:21:18,103 --> 00:21:19,481
and that's why I was holding you?

290
00:21:19,481 --> 00:21:21,033
And tell him not to get the wrong idea?

291
00:21:21,793 --> 00:21:22,655
Or maybe...

292
00:21:22,655 --> 00:21:24,344
I shouldn't have forced this on you.

293
00:21:30,447 --> 00:21:31,792
Tuo.

294
00:21:32,793 --> 00:21:34,482
Are you only with me...

295
00:21:35,965 --> 00:21:38,309
to humor me?

296
00:21:38,309 --> 00:21:39,757
Out of pity?

297
00:21:41,413 --> 00:21:43,378
Don't be ridiculous.

298
00:21:56,655 --> 00:21:57,896
Hello?

299
00:21:57,896 --> 00:21:58,896
Mom.

300
00:22:00,240 --> 00:22:01,344
What?

301
00:22:07,068 --> 00:22:08,275
Junxi.

302
00:22:08,275 --> 00:22:09,275
Over here.

303
00:22:14,931 --> 00:22:16,241
You can't even drink water.

304
00:22:16,585 --> 00:22:18,930
But I want some ice cream.

305
00:22:18,931 --> 00:22:20,723
This is no time for ice cream.

306
00:22:20,723 --> 00:22:21,723
Mom.

307
00:22:23,206 --> 00:22:24,620
Didn't Dad pass out?

308
00:22:25,344 --> 00:22:27,723
He was awake by the
time he got to the hospital.

309
00:22:28,619 --> 00:22:30,309
The doctor says it's gallstones.

310
00:22:30,309 --> 00:22:32,964
He's scheduled for minimally
invasive surgery tomorrow.

311
00:22:38,965 --> 00:22:39,965
Big Bro.

312
00:22:43,172 --> 00:22:44,619
I brought Dad's things.

313
00:22:44,619 --> 00:22:46,447
See if I missed anything.

314
00:22:54,931 --> 00:22:55,931
Mom.

315
00:22:56,447 --> 00:22:58,206
I'll stay with Dad tonight.

316
00:22:58,206 --> 00:22:59,619
You should go home and rest.

317
00:22:59,619 --> 00:23:00,895
Just come back tomorrow morning.

318
00:23:00,896 --> 00:23:01,758
That's right. That's right.

319
00:23:01,758 --> 00:23:03,413
It's nothing serious.

320
00:23:03,413 --> 00:23:04,930
You go home and get some rest.

321
00:23:05,378 --> 00:23:06,137
But...

322
00:23:06,137 --> 00:23:07,585
There are no buts.

323
00:23:07,585 --> 00:23:09,585
Just go home and rest. It's fine.

324
00:23:10,689 --> 00:23:12,481
All right, I know.

325
00:23:12,481 --> 00:23:15,826
Then you two have to get along, okay?

326
00:23:15,827 --> 00:23:17,378
No fighting.

327
00:23:17,378 --> 00:23:19,068
I'll come by tomorrow after class.

328
00:23:25,413 --> 00:23:26,413
Dad.

329
00:23:29,240 --> 00:23:31,240
You don't drink enough water.

330
00:23:32,240 --> 00:23:34,481
I'm so busy every day.
Who has time to drink water?

331
00:23:34,481 --> 00:23:35,619
I've got no one to help me.

332
00:23:35,619 --> 00:23:37,240
Mom, I'll go get some water.

333
00:23:37,240 --> 00:23:37,930
Okay.

334
00:23:37,931 --> 00:23:38,965
Get water for what?

335
00:23:38,965 --> 00:23:40,482
Your mom just said I can't drink any.

336
00:23:41,344 --> 00:23:42,964
Don't be mad.

337
00:23:42,965 --> 00:23:44,137
Just talk nicely.

338
00:23:44,172 --> 00:23:45,689
I'm getting it for Mom to drink.

339
00:23:50,068 --> 00:23:51,758
Get along.

340
00:23:51,758 --> 00:23:54,034
All right, stop nagging. Just stop.

341
00:24:06,309 --> 00:24:08,861
Looks like my brother hasn't
said anything to our parents yet.

342
00:24:10,103 --> 00:24:11,344
What a relief.

343
00:24:16,585 --> 00:24:18,481
What is wrong with me?

344
00:24:18,481 --> 00:24:20,275
My dad is sick in the hospital,

345
00:24:20,275 --> 00:24:21,861
and all I'm worried about is myself.

346
00:24:21,862 --> 00:24:23,240
My head is just full of thoughts about us,

347
00:24:23,240 --> 00:24:24,551
about whether we've been found out.

348
00:24:24,551 --> 00:24:25,723
I...

349
00:24:29,793 --> 00:24:30,793
I'm sorry.

350
00:24:35,481 --> 00:24:36,654
What are you doing?

351
00:24:48,551 --> 00:24:49,999
Let's break up.

352
00:26:35,896 --> 00:26:43,379
FOX
///*
/ +19 AD/
Jiamei Hotel Taipei/

353
00:27:00,862 --> 00:27:02,447
(Next episode preview)
Sacrificing yourself for the one you love.

354
00:27:02,447 --> 00:27:04,171
So noble of you, you coward.

355
00:27:06,862 --> 00:27:08,620
Lashing out because you're embarrassed?

356
00:27:09,827 --> 00:27:11,689
Why does love have to be so hard?

357
00:27:12,551 --> 00:27:15,275
What if our parents can't accept it?

358
00:27:15,275 --> 00:27:17,654
Could you still fight to be with Tuo?

359
00:27:21,689 --> 00:27:23,620
Mom.